name: JTrie
short_description: A Java Trie data structure implementation. Can be used as a dictionary for search of words. Insertion and deletion of words available. Only digits, English and Greek characters are supported. Supports also, the calculation of the minimum Levenshtein distance (edit distance) from all the words that exist inside the trie. The Levenshtein distance calculation benefits from the Trie data stucture and can be computed much faster than computing the distance for each word in the trie. See http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Trie for more informations about the Trie data structure.
summary: Java Trie implementation. Supports dictionary & edit distance.
